stylometry: Price and demand are related in different situations demand maybe more or less sensitive to change in price. This is called the price elasticity of demand. As prices for a product increases the demand for that product decreases. A company doesnt want to charge less than the cost of the unit, however. elascity of demand plays a role in the formula. So you can do a breakeven analysis and find out the price per unit in order to breakeven and from there only sell a product that will allow the company to either breakeven or create revenue.
